<item>
            <title>[FLINK-4559] Kinesis Producer not setting credentials provider properly when AWS_CREDENTIALS_PROVIDER is &quot;AUTO&quot;</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-4559</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If the &lt;tt&gt;AWS_CREDENTIAL_PROVIDER&lt;/tt&gt; option is set to &lt;tt&gt;AUTO&lt;/tt&gt;, &lt;tt&gt;AWSUtils.getCredentialsProvider&lt;/tt&gt; will return &lt;tt&gt;null&lt;/tt&gt;, so &lt;tt&gt;setCredentialsProvider&lt;/tt&gt; should not be explicitly called on the internally built &lt;tt&gt;KinesisProducerConfiguration&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13002122">FLINK-4559</key>
